From 525836f3956f7b5b83dfc83e38cf0a9d713236f7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mike Ma <mike.ma@lmctl.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 10:19:43 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Treat predictable-branch threshold as inclusive in
 SelectOptimize

`isSelectHighlyPredictable` compared branch probability with a strict `>`,
which excluded the exact threshold value (`99/100` by default). That misses
the `__builtin_expect_with_probability(..., 0.99)` boundary case after
metadata lowering.

Use an inclusive comparison so threshold-equal probabilities are considered
highly predictable, and extend X86 select-optimize coverage to lock both the
equal-threshold and below-threshold behaviors.

Tested: cmake -S llvm -B build-selectopt -G Ninja -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DLLVM_ENABLE_PROJECTS= -DLLVM_TARGETS_TO_BUILD=X86 -DLLVM_INCLUDE_EXAMPLES=OFF -DLLVM_INCLUDE_DOCS=OFF -DLLVM_INCLUDE_BENCHMARKS=OFF -DLLVM_INCLUDE_TESTS=ON -DLLVM_BUILD_TESTS=OFF -DLLVM_BUILD_TOOLS=ON
Tested: ninja -C build-selectopt opt FileCheck count not llvm-config llc
Tested: build-selectopt/bin/llvm-lit -sv llvm/test/CodeGen/X86/select-optimize.ll
